GameStartupGuide:
• Just proceed as instructed in the 'Start the Game' section if you are not playing the game for the first time.
  • If you had enabled gadget block bypass setting, you could turn it off now since no regional restriction any more.
  • If you don't have a game account yet, follow a tutorial and finish the registration and server selection with KC3改 off.
GameHotkeyHUD: Hold to show KC3改 Special HUD
GameHotkeyType: Get 20 seconds of keyboard typing time
GameAltDMMInfo: If you're here, you're already set to play via the DMM website. This is our recommended mode. Don't forget— you have to turn on 'Apply Customizations' first to get on-screen customizations like subtitles, translations and backgrounds.
GameAltFrameInfo: Since HTTPS upgrade, DMM on frame not allowed by security policy. For Flash phase, in some Chrome versions (55+), the DMM Frame doesn't render. It only shows a black screen, but you can hear sounds.
GameAltAPIInfo: Since December 2024, game settings are saved into their servers, API Link works again. Hostname has started to use server's own domain instead of IP address.
GameAltIgnore: I am aware that this may not work, but I still want to open it.
GameStep2: In the DevTools panel that opened, click on the KanColle tab. Check the » pull-down menu if it's not visible.
GameStepHintRam: To reduce RAM usage, switch to the Network tab, click the red 🔴 button or press Ctrl E in order to stop the recording log.
GameStepHintHttps: If your browser forced to upgrade later opened DMM site to HTTPS connection (there will be a lock icon 🔒 on the left of omnibus bar), click the lock icon; choose web site settings menu; find and set to 'allow insecure content'; then restart the game tab.
GameDMMRedirect: You will be redirected to play directly on DMM website
GameDMMFrame: iFrame mode does NOT work any more thank to DMM page cross-domain security policy

SettingsBrokenTip: Partially not working as expected since game has been changed.
SettingsCheckNewShipFromDexTip: In order to highlight dropped or built or library ship girls that you don't already own, we need to access all pages of the in-game Ship Library once to gather relevant data. If we do not check it via the Library, ships that have been fed, scrapped or sunk are still considered to be new ships. To update highlights of Equipment Library list, the in-game library pages have to be accessed on new equpment obtained.
SettingsPowerCriticalTip: Critical power will not be available if Post-cap above is not enabled.
SettingsSSDirDesc: This sets a target location within your browser's /Download/ directory for the downloaded file. Subdirectories can be assigned, but absolute paths, empty paths and paths containing back-references ('..') will produce an error. The location of the /Download/ directory itself is determined by your browser's settings.
SettingsIdleWarnDesc: Time in seconds before idle screen shows, 0 for disable.
SettingsDisableHasDameconTip: Having this activated will cause the Taiha Alert NOT to appear when a ship that is still equipping any type of Damecon is in a taiha state. Advance Button Blocker will NOT appear if a taiha ship is equipping a Damecon that has not been consumed yet, irrelevant to this option.
SettingsDisableUnlockShipsTip: Having this activated will cause the Taiha Alert and Advance Button Blocker NOT to appear when a ship that has not been heart-locked is in a taiha state. Advance Button Blocker will still appear if the ship is holding any locked equipment.
SettingsNextBlockerTip:
Enabling this feature will help prevent the user from pressing the advance button when there is a taiha ship in the fleet.

This doesn't mean you shouldn't pay attention to the HP levels of your ships! Please be aware that if there are any battle API changes, such changes may cause the advance button block to fail in unexpecteded ways. If any such API changes are observed, it is advisable to disable this option in order to avoid unfortunate mistakes.

Please note that "Block w/Fairy" mode requires the in-game sound option "SE" to be unmuted. "Block w/Fairy" mode will automatically enter "Block w/o Fairy" mode instead if the in-game "SE" is muted. Note that the game can still be freely muted in the panel without affecting "SE mode".
SettingsNextBlockerSecondFSTip: Having this activated will cause the Advance Button Blocker to still appear when the escort flagship of a combined fleet is in a taiha state.
SettingsFocusGameTabTip: This option shifts focus to the game window both when the first damage cut-in of a battle occurs and when a battle has ended. Please note that it will only work when the in-game home port sound option 'SE' is enabled. This option will still work if the game is muted out of game, such as by using the KC3 panel's mute toggle or by muting the browser's tab.

SubtitleDisplayStick: (Stick) Fixed on the bottom of browser window

SettingsDMMRedirectGadgetTip:
Enable this if you get a white screen with HTTP 403 error messages upon starting the game. Don't enable this if you're already behind a proxy, such as a Japanese VPN or KCCacheProxy.
Disable this and enable a proxy when access non-game pages such as registration, ranking. Otherwise, you will get HTTP 404 errors.

Explanation:
KanColle has a gadget server, which sends metadata required for connecting to the game—namely, the game version and the server's address. The KanColle regional block may prevent access to this based on where you're connecting from. The Gadget Block Bypass option will reroute traffic to a public cache server in an attempt to allow the game to load without denying access.
SettingsDMMGadgetCacheUrlTip:
The current default public cache server for the Gadget Block Bypass option is hosted on `kcwiki.github.io`, which is regularly updated by an English KanColle wiki administrator. This option allows you to configure the Gadget Block Bypass to use an alternate public server in the interest of updating the game more efficiently or for improving connection speed. Note that you may experience additional lag when updating the game's cache following a game update.

Only input the initial part of the cache server's URL—everything before the `/gadget_html5/` subdirectory. For example, if attemping to use

`http://luckyjervis.com/gadget_html5/js/kcs_const.js` 

you will need to enter this into the field:

`http://luckyjervis.com/`
SettingsDMMCustomCSSTip: Valid CSS3 declarations. Don't change this if you are not familiar with CSS and DMM sources. To see changes, reload DMM game page. Don't forget that sometimes `!important` is needed to overwrite defaults.
SettingsPanelColorTip: The default format uses rgba(red (0-255), green (0-255), blue(0-255), opacity(0.00-1.00)). Setting the fourth number (opacity) to 0 will disable the color.
SettingsPanelCustomCSSTip: Valid CSS3 declarations. Don't change this if you are not familiar with CSS and KC3 sources. Changes will be applied immediately on this field saved. Don't forget that sometimes `!important` is needed to overwrite defaults.
SettingsPanelPvPFriendsTip: List of user names of friends to be highlighted in PvP panel. Names should be seperated with lines. You can also click on a name in the PvP panel to toggle friend highlighting for that player.
SettingsPanelReloadReminderStartTip: Show a reminder after specific time to reopen Chrome devtools panels in order to release memory taken by game tab process. 0 = disable
SettingsPanelReloadReminderStartRepeatTi: Show the reminder every specific time after first one, 0 = only once
SettingsPanelPortSoundNotifyEventOnly: Home Port Notification for Event Map Change Only

SettingsStrategyCustomCSSTip: Valid CSS3 declarations. Don't change this if you are not familiar with CSS and KC3 sources. To see changes, reload Strategy Room page. Don't forget that sometimes `!important` is needed to overwrite defaults.
SettingsMaxEventTagsTip: Recommend keeping it 'Auto'. But when new event starts and before auto update comes to, you may set this to larger value if amount of locking tags is not enough for Locking Planner page. Colors of tags can be changed via Custom CSS.
SettingsSaveSortieToDbTip: Don't disable this if you don't want your Maps / Events History miss your battle data. Disabling this will also make Ledger can not search your sortie related consumptions by maps.
SettingsSaveSortieButMapsTip: Set a list to exclude maps from saving sortie battle data. Format: [map ID1, map ID2, ...]. For example: [11,15,54] means do not save data sortied to 1-1, 1-5, 5-4. Will not save any map if previous option disabled.
SettingsSavePvpToDbTip: Don't disable this if you don't want your PvP Battle History miss your data.
SettingsConsoleLogHooksTip: Stop KC3's internal logging from watching chrome's console methods. This option is primarily for developers; generally, it should remain unticked.
SettingsLogKeepDurationTip: Specify the amount of time after which regular logs (log, debug, info) will be automatically discarded.
SettingsErrorKeepDurationTip: Specify the amount of time after which error logs (warn, error) will be automatically discarded.
